Privacy Policy for Plain Site
**Last Updated: March 30, 2026

Introduction
Plain Site (“we,” “our,” or “us”) is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, store, and protect your information when you use the Plain Site mobile application Plain Site.

By using Plain Site, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.

Information We Collect
Information You Provide Directly
When you use Plain Site, you may choose to provide:

Personal Information: Names, phone numbers, addresses, dates of birth, emergency contact details
Health Information: Medical intake information, insurance details (if you choose to store them)
Documents: Photos of ID cards, insurance cards, vaccination records, and other documents you upload
Custom Data: Any other information you manually enter into the app
Important: You control what information you provide. Plain Site does not require you to enter any specific information to use the app.

Information Collected Automatically
Usage Data: How you interact with the app (which features you use, when you use them)
Device Information: Device type, operating system version, unique device identifiers
Error Logs: Crash reports and error logs to help us improve the app
Information We Do NOT Collect
We do NOT access your contacts, camera, or microphone without your explicit permission
We do NOT track your location
We do NOT collect browsing history
We do NOT share your data with third-party advertisers
How We Use Your Information
We use the information you provide to:

Provide Core Functionality: Store and organize your personal information for form-filling purposes
Cloud Sync (Optional): If you sign in with Firebase Authentication, sync your data across devices
Improve the App: Analyze usage patterns to enhance features and fix bugs
Customer Support: Respond to your questions and provide assistance
Security: Protect against unauthorized access and ensure data integrity
We will NEVER sell your personal information to third parties.

How We Store Your Information
Local Storage (Default Mode)
By default, Plain Site stores all your data locally on your device:

Data is saved using encrypted local storage
No data leaves your device unless you explicitly choose cloud sync
Data remains on your device even if you’re offline
Cloud Storage (Optional)
If you choose to enable cloud sync by signing in:

Your data is stored securely in Firebase Firestore (Google Cloud Platform)
Files are stored in Firebase Storage
Data is encrypted in transit using industry-standard SSL/TLS
Data is encrypted at rest on Google’s servers
You can delete your cloud data at any time from the Settings screen
Data Security
We take your security seriously and implement multiple protection measures:

Encryption: All data transmitted to our servers is encrypted using SSL/TLS
Firebase Security Rules: Cloud data is protected by strict access controls
No Plaintext Passwords: We use Firebase Authentication (no passwords stored by us)
Regular Security Reviews: We regularly audit our security practices
Local-First Design: Your data can stay entirely on your device if you prefer
However, no method of electronic storage is 100% secure. While we strive to protect your data, we cannot guarantee absolute security.

Data Retention
Local Data
Data stored locally remains on your device until you manually delete it
Uninstalling the app will remove all local data
Cloud Data
Data stored in Firebase remains until you delete your account
You can delete your account and all associated data from the Settings screen
Deleted data is permanently removed within 30 days
Your Rights and Choices
You have the following rights regarding your data:

Access and Portability
Export Your Data: Use the “Backup Your Data” feature in Settings to export all your information as a JSON file
Download: Save your backup file to your device, iCloud, or email it to yourself
Deletion
Delete Individual Items: Remove specific individuals, templates, or files at any time
Clear All Local Data: Use “Clear local data” in Settings
Delete Your Account: Use “Delete My Account” in Settings to permanently delete all data (both local and cloud)
Control Cloud Sync
Sign Out: Disconnect from cloud sync at any time
Local Mode: Use the app entirely offline without creating an account
Opt-Out of Analytics (Future)
If we add analytics in the future, you will have the ability to opt out
Children’s Privacy
Plain Site is designed for use by adults to manage information about themselves and others (including children in their care, such as for daycare forms).

We do NOT knowingly collect personal information from children under 13 without parental consent. If you are a parent or guardian managing information about your child, you are responsible for the information you enter.

If you believe we have inadvertently collected information from a child under 13, please contact us immediately at [YOUR EMAIL].

Third-Party Services
Plain Site uses the following third-party services:

Firebase (Google Cloud Platform)
Purpose: Cloud storage and authentication (optional)
Data Shared: Only if you enable cloud sync
Privacy Policy: https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy
Expo
Purpose: App development framework
Data Shared: Error logs and crash reports
Privacy Policy: https://expo.dev/privacy
We do NOT use:

Third-party advertising networks
Analytics tracking (beyond basic usage statistics)
Social media integrations
International Data Transfers
If you use cloud sync, your data may be stored on servers located in the United States or other countries where Google Cloud Platform operates. By using cloud sync, you consent to the transfer of your data to these locations.

Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do:

We will update the “Last Updated” date at the top
We will notify you through the app (if possible)
Continued use of the app after changes constitutes acceptance
We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically.

Contact Us
If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or how we handle your data:

Email: plainsite@techsortie.com
App: Plain Site

Your Consent
By using Plain Site, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this Privacy Policy and agree to its terms.

California Residents: Under the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), you have additional rights. Contact us for more information about exercising these rights.

European Users: Under GDPR, you have the right to access, rectify, erase, and port your data. Contact us to exercise these rights.

Summary (Plain Language)
What we collect: Only the information you choose to enter (names, phone numbers, addresses, documents)

How we use it: To help you fill out forms faster by storing your information

Where it’s stored: On your device by default, or optionally in secure cloud storage (Firebase)

Who we share with: Nobody. We don’t sell or share your data.

Your control: You can export or delete your data anytime

Questions?: Email us at plainsite@techsortie.com

This Privacy Policy was last updated on March 30, 2026 and is effective immediately.

